# DomainModel Best Practices

**Template**: [DomainModel.hbs](mdc:docs/technical/templates/domain-templates/DomainModel.hbs)

## Purpose
Domain models are **entity classes** that represent business objects. They inherit from `Entity` base class.

## Requirements

- **Inherit from Entity**: Provides `Id`, `CreatedAt`, `UpdatedAt`, `IsDeleted`
- **Table attribute**: Use `[Table("snake_case_name")]` for Dapper mapping
- **Column attributes**: Use `[Column("snake_case")]` on all properties
- **Public class**: Models are public for use across layers
- **Simple properties**: No business logic in models

## Pattern

```csharp
using System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.Schema;

namespace Platform.Domain;

[Table("features")]
public class Feature : Entity
{
    [Column("name")]
    public string Name { get; set; } = string.Empty;

    [Column("description")]
    public string? Description { get; set; }

    [Column("is_active")]
    public bool IsActive { get; set; }
}
```

## Entity Base Class Provides

- `Id` (Guid) - Primary key
- `CreatedAt` (DateTime) - Set by database
- `UpdatedAt` (DateTime) - Set by database
- `IsDeleted` (bool) - Soft delete flag

## Do NOT

- Add methods or business logic to models
- Forget Column attributes (breaks Dapper mapping)
- Use different naming than snake_case for database columns
